description.plain:
16 year old singer/songwriter, half Icelandic and from a family of musicians and artists. She plays electric guitar and will mess around on the piano while writing. Claire writes all of her own songs and produces them in the studio with her dad Ragnar. She was born and raised in Southern California and released her debut EP, BeVerly Hills BoYfRiEnsd on June 9th, 2020 across all streaming platforms. The artist first gained a following on popular social media app, TikTok, where she teased some of her songs and was met with eager viewers, all ready to jam out to her new music..
Claire’s music is experimental blues pop and is excited to release much more in hopes that people can relate as well as vibe out to her songs
(from her spotify about)

songs.title: Backyard Boy

description.plain: Backyard Boy is the fourth song on 16-year-old artist Claire Rosinkranz’s debut EP, BeVerly Hills BoYfRiEnd. She released the EP June 6th, although she gave the first look at “Backyard Boy” on May 23rd through the app TikTok, the social media platform on which this song was later popularized by.

songs.title: ​don’t miss me

description.plain:
don’t miss me is the lead single off Rosinkranz’s album, CR1*. It explores committment issues on the cusp of a potential new relationship. Claire has said that this song is about her own issues committing to significant others.

don’t miss me has also inspired a tiktok trend where people upload photos of themselves next to the lyrics of the song.
